cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a decision problem related to graph theory and combinatorics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents novel algorithmic results for solving the Disconnected Cut problem on certain graph classes.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper deals with graph decompositions and characterizations of certain subgraphs.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper deals with graph cuts, which are relevant in game theory and network design.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of the Disconnected Cut problem on different graph classes.
